{
  "text": "Vascular relaxation in response to µM concentrations of oestrogen is not different in wild-type mice compared with mice lacking a functional ERα indicating that ERβ might be responsible [CITATION_1] . The aim of the present study was to investigate the importance of ERβ for relaxation caused by pharmacological concentrations of oestrogen by using arterial preparations from mice lacking functional ERβ.",
